==English==

===Etymology===

Neo-Latin [[ostracum#Latin|ostracum]], from Greek [[ὄστρακον]], originally meaning "pottery fragment" and later extended to refer to shells.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|ostraca}}

# {{context|archaeology}} a fragment of pottery.
# {{context|malacology}} the middle layer of a molluscan shell.

